 very close friend of their family was murdered by terrorists earlier this year.  This was the family where the wife was rescued, but the husband was killed.  This was upsetting for our friends, and now they get to worry about her parents on top of that.  Another one of my friends has parents who are missionaries in Indonesia.  I can't say their mission is all negative because my friend is Indonesian, and her parents adopted her and brought her here to the states to live a normal life instead of one of poverty.  However, they are right back in Indonesia where it is dangerous.  My friend isn't religious, so needless to say she is living right here in the good ole USA.  I've met both sets of parents, and I know they mean well at heart.  However, they are putting a lot of worry on their children by putting their lives in danger like that, and they are potentially putting other people in danger if they need rescuing.  If they were just there to help in a secular fashion, then there would still be some dangers, but not as many as when they are trying to pass their religion around.  This tactic angers people who might not normally be angered by their presence.  <br>
<br>
