<br>
The LDS philosophy is that we dont proselytize in any country that doesnt want us there.  But we also have the belief that all who don't have to opportunity to hear the gospel in this life will have the opporunity in the spirit world before they are resurrected, so we do not feel that if we dont go there they will be damned.<br>
<br>
From the perspective of a religion that feels that it is absolutely necessary for a person to hear and accept the gospel of Jesus Christ in this life or else they will be damned, missionary work is the only compassionate thing to do.  It is the way to help save your fellow brothers and sisters.  <br>
<br>
If a person is truly convicted in their beliefs, it would be illogical to accept that it is ok to not &quot;witness&quot; to someone because they already have a religion.  Part of beleiving in your faith is the belief that what you believe is true and as in science truth is absolute.  <br>
<br>
